  "text": "Electrostatic potential surface calculations support the preferential selectivity of the central pores of CsoS1A and CcmK4 for anions over nonpolar molecules. Time-averaged electrostatic potentials of the protein complexes were calculated using the structures of the protein hexamers generated from the last 10 ns of the equilibrium simulations (Fig. 7) . The calculated electrostatic potential surfaces are consistent with ones previously calculated using the crystal structures [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , supporting the idea that the pores are highly charged.",
